# .WORKTREEINCLUDE - Git Worktree File Inclusions
# ================================================
#
# Location: Project root as `.worktreeinclude`
# Purpose: Specify gitignored files to copy into new git worktrees
# Commit: YES - Share with team
#
# WHAT IS THIS FOR?
# =================
#
# Git worktrees allow checking out multiple branches simultaneously.
# By default, gitignored files (like .env) are NOT copied to new worktrees.
#
# This file lists gitignored files that SHOULD be copied when creating
# a new worktree.
#
# USE CASES
# =========
#
# 1. ENVIRONMENT TEMPLATES:
#    You have .env.example that developers copy to .env
#    The example file should exist in all worktrees
#
# 2. DOCKER COMPOSE OVERRIDES:
#    You have docker-compose.override.yml.example
#    Each worktree needs this template
#
# 3. IDE SETTINGS:
#    You have .vscode/settings.json.example
#    Each worktree gets the template
#
# 4. LOCAL CONFIG TEMPLATES:
#    Any .example or .template files developers need to copy
#
# WHAT TO LIST HERE
# =================
#
# List files that:
# - Are gitignored (or would be)
# - Should exist in every worktree
# - Are templates/examples (not real secrets!)
#
# DO NOT list:
# - Real credential files (.env with actual values)
# - Real secret files
# - Files with sensitive data
#
# EXAMPLE ENTRIES
# ===============
#
# Environment templates:
# .env.example
# .env.local.example
# .env.development.example
#
# Docker configuration:
# docker-compose.override.yml.example
# Dockerfile.local.example
#
# IDE settings:
# .vscode/settings.json.example
# .idea/runConfigurations/example.xml
#
# Local config:
# config/local.json.example
# settings.local.example.yml
#
# HOW GIT WORKTREES WORK
# ======================
#
# Creating a new worktree:
#   git worktree add ../feature-branch-name
#
# This:
# 1. Creates a new directory at ../feature-branch-name
# 2. Checks out the specified branch there
# 3. Copies files listed in .worktreeinclude
#
# EXAMPLE COMPLETE FILE
# =====================
#
# # Environment templates
# .env.example
# .env.local.example
# .env.test.example
#
# # Docker
# docker-compose.override.yml.example
# Dockerfile.development
#
# # IDE
# .vscode/settings.json.example
# .vscode/launch.json.example
#
# # Config
# config/database.yml.example
# config/local.json.example
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ==================
#
# 1. Copy this template to `.worktreeinclude`
# 2. List template/example files your team needs
# 3. Ensure listed files don't contain real secrets
# 4. Commit to git
#
# NOTES
# =====
#
# - These are TEMPLATES, not real config files
# - Developers copy and customize them in each worktree
# - This ensures templates exist everywhere they're needed
# - Real .env files stay gitignored and NOT copied
